# WhataHotel proposals — copy and labels

Before changing **`PromoPage.tsx`**, **`ComparisonOverview.tsx`**, **`ProposalInvestment.tsx`**, or **`gift`** feature blocks in **`src/data/promo-*.ts`**, read **`docs/whatahotel-design-ssot.md`** section **“Client-approved copy & labels (do not regress)”**.

## Required behavior

- **Exclusive Perks** (`PromoPage`): heading exactly that (capital **P**). No “& inclusions”, no Lorraine Travel subline under the section. Bullets = deduped `gift` `items[]` only.
- **`gift` feature `title` in data:** always **`"Exclusive Perks"`**. Do not use `WhataHotel! Exclusive Perks`, `Exclusive Perks & Inclusions`, or partner wording in `title`.
- **Rate table** (`ComparisonOverview`): user-facing heading **Rate Comparisons** — do not restore “Booking summary” / “Comparison overview” as visible copy.
- **Room pricing block** (`ProposalInvestment`): heading **Rate & pricing breakdown** only. No “Investment summary”. No per-room “Preferred Partner” / “What A Hotel! · Preferred Partner” line.
- **Footer:** org-level lines stay in **`ContactFooter`** / **`contact.ts`**; that is not the same as the removed per-room partner line.

Netlify agents: scope is usually data-only (`promo-N.ts`, `promos.ts`); still follow the **`gift` title** rule and avoid prose that duplicates removed UI. Paste **`docs/netlify-agent-project-context.txt`** into Netlify Project context.
